# Implement Real Authentication

This plan outlines the steps to connect the existing mock Login and Register UI to your Supabase backend using `@supabase/ssr`. 

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Email Confirmations:** By default, Supabase requires users to confirm their email before they can fully log in. This plan assumes email confirmations are enabled and includes the setup of an `auth/callback` route to handle the verification link users will receive in their email. If you have disabled email confirmations in your Supabase dashboard, let me know, as the post-registration flow will be slightly different (immediate login vs. "check your email" message).

## Proposed Changes

### Auth Middleware & Routing

To guarantee that the user's session is securely maintained throughout the website (and refreshed appropriately), we will add a Next.js `middleware.ts` and a callback route.

#### [NEW] [middleware.ts](file:///C:/Users/DELL/Documents/cinelist/middleware.ts)
- Implement Supabase's recommended session refresh using `@supabase/ssr` to ensure server components have access to the latest auth state.
- Configure the matcher to run on relevant routes.

#### [NEW] [app/api/auth/callback/route.ts](file:///C:/Users/DELL/Documents/cinelist/app/api/auth/callback/route.ts)
- Create a route to exchange the secure auth `code` (sent to users in their email) for a live session cookie, then redirect them to the home page or a confirmation page.

---

### Authentication Pages

We will swap out the `setTimeout` mocks with actual Supabase client invocations, capturing and displaying error/success messages.

#### [MODIFY] [login/page.tsx](file:///C:/Users/DELL/Documents/cinelist/app/%28auth%29/login/page.tsx)
- Import `createClient` from `@/lib/supabase/client`.
- Add an `error` state string to display failed login attempts (e.g. wrong password).
- Update `handleLogin` to call `await supabase.auth.signInWithPassword({ email, password })`.
- On success, redirect the user to the `/explore` or Home page.

#### [MODIFY] [register/page.tsx](file:///C:/Users/DELL/Documents/cinelist/app/%28auth%29/register/page.tsx)
- Import `createClient` from `@/lib/supabase/client`.
- Add `error` and `success` state strings.
- Update `handleRegister` to call `await supabase.auth.signUp(...)` with the `username` passed into `options.data`.
- On success, inform the user to check their email for a verification link (or redirect if email confirmation is disabled).

